      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was looking at some photos of deep space tonight and it just hit me how incredibly stupid it all is. like, everything we do, every single struggle, every bit of pain we go through... it’s just a tiny flicker of noise in an infinite, cold vacuum that doesn't even know we're here. it feels like we're all just performing this exhausting play for an audience of zero. does any of it actually mean anything to you, or is it all just empty?",
